WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:33.920 --> 02:35.679
It's loose.

02:35.680 --> 02:37.842
Chill, I'm not done.

02:39.160 --> 02:41.367
Would I let Boss down?

02:41.720 --> 02:42.679
It's true.

02:42.680 --> 02:44.125
My brother only trusts you.

02:44.126 --> 02:45.087
Right.

02:49.520 --> 02:52.319
He tells me "left", I go left.

02:52.320 --> 02:54.368
He tells me "right", I go right.

02:54.369 --> 02:57.011
Why doesn't he trust me?

02:57.240 --> 02:58.559
Like "lefty-loosey,

02:58.560 --> 03:00.199
righty-tighty".

03:00.200 --> 03:02.559
Your left may not be his left.

03:02.560 --> 03:05.039
Your right may not be his right.

03:05.040 --> 03:06.041
Busy talking?

03:06.760 --> 03:08.125
Let's move, one to each car.

03:08.126 --> 03:08.999
Get going!

03:09.000 --> 03:09.922
HEY

03:10.600 --> 03:12.125
The guy my brother trusts.

03:12.240 --> 03:12.919
Yeah?

03:12.920 --> 03:14.410
He wants you to join him.

03:14.411 --> 03:15.162
Okay.

03:41.120 --> 03:41.719
Go ahead.

03:41.720 --> 03:43.848
They drove off in three taxis

03:44.120 --> 03:45.446
with bombs in each one.

03:45.447 --> 03:46.441
Where did they go?

03:46.442 --> 03:47.399
Unsure.

03:47.400 --> 03:49.687
Two Toyotas, one Nissan.

03:50.080 --> 03:52.639
"DB 2436"

03:55.120 --> 03:58.044
"FA 969"

03:59.040 --> 04:00.804
Why does my brother trust him, not me?

04:01.040 --> 04:03.122
I don't trust him at all.

04:04.840 --> 04:06.285
Peng Hong is very cautious

04:06.286 --> 04:08.159
I don't know his plan yet.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.161
Stay in touch.

04:09.640 --> 04:11.319
He made three car bombs.

04:11.320 --> 04:12.890
All three are taxis.

04:13.240 --> 04:15.004
There are over 20,000 taxis in Hong Kong.

04:15.240 --> 04:16.446
Here are the license plate numbers.

04:50.040 --> 04:52.247
Have a drink, let's celebrate first.

05:08.680 --> 05:10.759
We lost the GPS signal of JS.

05:10.760 --> 05:11.719
Keep tracking.

05:11.720 --> 05:12.881
Have you located the three taxis?

05:12.882 --> 05:13.881
Not yet, sir.

05:23.640 --> 05:24.926
We'll be rich!

05:57.240 --> 05:58.287
Hey! Stop there!

06:21.200 --> 06:22.159
All Units,

06:22.160 --> 06:23.844
Heung To Bank Gold Vault is being attacked.

06:24.800 --> 06:27.201
Sir, Heung To Bank is being attacked.

06:27.202 --> 06:28.247
All units, take action.

06:28.248 --> 06:29.048
Yes, sir.

06:57.560 --> 06:58.971
Bring another cart.

07:21.240 --> 07:22.366
It smells great.

08:17.520 --> 08:19.761
Don't lose them.

08:30.280 --> 08:31.964
Crash into him... Go ahead.

08:46.760 --> 08:47.886
Fun, JS?

08:51.680 --> 08:52.719
Slow down...

08:52.720 --> 08:53.403
- Let them catch up.
- Yes.

08:53.404 --> 08:54.561
Let them catch up.

08:55.120 --> 08:56.007
They're coming.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.839
Brother, did you see that?

09:13.840 --> 09:15.046
I did it.

09:20.600 --> 09:22.090
Calling Control. Officer down.

09:22.091 --> 09:22.763
Hurry.

09:38.920 --> 09:39.959
All units, stop.

09:39.960 --> 09:41.200
Do not enter the car park.

09:41.320 --> 09:42.765
Beware of car bombs.

10:07.040 --> 10:08.371
Go around to block them.

10:13.640 --> 10:14.687
What the heck?

10:29.560 --> 10:30.368
Stop.

10:41.240 --> 10:42.685
Put your gun down.

10:43.200 --> 10:44.565
Put your gun down

10:45.040 --> 10:46.164
I order you to put your gun down.

10:46.165 --> 10:47.002
- Police.
- Put your gun down.

10:47.003 --> 10:48.411
Put down your weapons, freeze

10:48.412 --> 10:50.243
I said, put your gun down.

10:52.880 --> 10:53.449
Get out of the car.

10:54.720 --> 10:55.881
Hands up.

10:56.280 --> 10:57.725
- Turn that way.
- Stop.

10:57.800 --> 10:59.768
Set him free, he is our man.

11:01.360 --> 11:03.362
My elder brother will come and save me.

11:05.560 --> 11:07.199
Traitor.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.009
He will never stop hunting you down.

11:09.840 --> 11:11.251
- He definitely will come to save me.
- Take him away.

11:11.252 --> 11:13.208
He won't let you off the hook.

11:19.120 --> 11:20.531
They entered the pedestrian tunnel

11:20.880 --> 11:22.689
Roger, we'll go block them from the front.

12:04.360 --> 12:05.361
Scumbag.

12:06.240 --> 12:07.366
Scumbag.

12:18.200 --> 12:19.440
Sir, a bomb!

12:51.960 --> 12:52.839
Listen up.

12:52.840 --> 12:55.081
Please put your cell phones in the locker

12:55.082 --> 12:56.570
together with any flash drives

12:56.571 --> 12:57.319
or lighters.

12:57.320 --> 12:57.969
Thank you very much.

12:58.280 --> 12:59.008
Thank you, sir.

13:00.640 --> 13:01.923
Plastic explosives,

13:01.924 --> 13:02.762
as its name implies,

13:02.763 --> 13:05.331
can be formed into different shapes,

13:05.560 --> 13:08.131
making them difficult to be detected.

13:08.200 --> 13:10.089
Even x-ray machines cannot detect them.

13:10.240 --> 13:11.287
One kind of plastic explosives is.

13:11.288 --> 13:13.599
Composition C-4.

13:13.600 --> 13:16.639
Its power of damage is greater than TNT.

13:16.640 --> 13:17.448
Its explosive velocity

13:17.449 --> 13:19.522
can be up to 8km per second.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.086
This is a dummy of the American-made model.

13:22.087 --> 13:24.799
MKII fragmentation-type hand grenade.

13:24.800 --> 13:25.684
It weighs 600 grams

13:25.685 --> 13:27.565
and is filled with 6O grams of TNT.

13:27.566 --> 13:29.164
It has a safety pin inside.

13:29.440 --> 13:31.522
If I pull it out and let go.

13:32.120 --> 13:33.879
The striker spring

13:33.880 --> 13:35.405
will bump against the detonator inside

13:35.406 --> 13:36.999
ignition will occur,

13:37.000 --> 13:40.125
the grenade will explode
in a delay of 3.2 to 4 seconds

13:40.126 --> 13:41.770
with a lethal range of 3 meters.

13:42.280 --> 13:42.999
Yes.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.284
If the hand grenade is held in hand

13:44.285 --> 13:45.361
with the safety pin removed

13:45.362 --> 13:47.283
then the grenade will not explode, correct?

13:47.284 --> 13:48.247
Correct.

13:49.720 --> 13:51.165
But I am curious.

13:51.720 --> 13:53.126
Why wouldn't you let it go?

13:53.127 --> 13:54.565
It's not a girl's hand.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.922
But in case you're so unfortunate

13:57.923 --> 14:01.049
to be holding a hand grenade
without a safety pin.

14:01.360 --> 14:02.247
Remember

14:06.680 --> 14:08.762
you must hold on to it like a girl's hand.

14:08.763 --> 14:10.319
Don't let go so easily.

14:10.320 --> 14:11.367
Thank you.

14:12.840 --> 14:14.410
We, the Explosive Ordinance Disposal unit,

14:14.411 --> 14:16.801
work in teams of two during operations.

14:16.880 --> 14:18.206
This is Superintendent JS Cheung.

14:18.207 --> 14:19.770
He is Bomb Disposal Number One.

14:19.771 --> 14:20.919
As Number Two,

14:20.920 --> 14:23.204
my job is to assist Number One to complete

14:23.205 --> 14:25.122
the mission as safely
and quickly as possible.

14:25.123 --> 14:27.599
If a hand grenade lands in front of me

14:27.600 --> 14:29.648
but it doesn't explode after 4 seconds

14:29.720 --> 14:30.721
what shall I do?

14:30.722 --> 14:31.881
You should thank God

14:31.882 --> 14:33.530
and run away.

14:33.680 --> 14:34.522
No, it should be

14:34.523 --> 14:37.046
run first, and then thank God.

14:49.520 --> 14:50.519
Officer Cheung.

14:50.520 --> 14:52.363
Today is your lucky day.

14:53.200 --> 14:54.919
Every day is my lucky day

14:54.920 --> 14:56.922
I like more academic girls.

14:58.120 --> 14:58.962
Hello.

14:59.240 --> 15:01.039
My handbag was just here.

15:01.040 --> 15:01.764
Give it back to me.

15:01.765 --> 15:03.602
Sweetie, we didn't take your handbag.

15:03.603 --> 15:06.043
My ID card, money, everything is inside.

15:06.044 --> 15:07.279
It's very important

15:07.280 --> 15:09.681
I understand, but I really didn't take it.

15:10.000 --> 15:11.684
Then where is my handbag?

15:12.800 --> 15:14.131
Go look somewhere else.

15:17.960 --> 15:19.041
Stop.

15:19.520 --> 15:23.119
Boys and girls, attention please.

15:23.120 --> 15:26.279
If anyone finds a yellow handbag...

15:26.280 --> 15:28.851
Officer Cheung, maybe you
should take her away.

15:29.560 --> 15:31.045
You can't drink until you're 18.

15:31.046 --> 15:32.087
Show me your ID card.

15:53.160 --> 15:54.400
Are you going there?

16:02.960 --> 16:04.039
Who is she?

16:04.040 --> 16:05.963
Officer Cheung from EOD brought her here.

16:06.240 --> 16:07.839
Is he from Anti-vice?

16:07.840 --> 16:09.602
Why would he bring a drunken whore here?

16:09.603 --> 16:10.647
How would I know?

16:12.120 --> 16:14.009
Officer Cheung, she's coming to.

16:14.440 --> 16:15.399
Please be kind.

16:15.400 --> 16:16.890
Don't call her a drunken whore.

16:17.720 --> 16:18.759
Sorry, sir.

16:18.760 --> 16:19.921
You were so excited

16:20.240 --> 16:21.844
you forgot I am in the chat group too.

16:21.920 --> 16:23.039
She is drunk

16:23.040 --> 16:24.565
but not a whore.

16:43.440 --> 16:44.805
Diameter: 14 (inches)

16:45.520 --> 16:46.931
Length: 44 (inches)

16:47.240 --> 16:49.527
It's a war-time aerial
bomb filled with TNT.

16:49.528 --> 16:51.249
Model number M64.

16:51.440 --> 16:52.759
With a nose fuse.

16:52.760 --> 16:54.171
Standard weight is 500 pounds.

16:54.172 --> 16:56.319
This device can destroy a tank.

16:56.320 --> 16:57.287
That's true.

16:57.880 --> 16:59.120
And it's very unstable.

16:59.360 --> 17:01.647
Immediately evacuate nearby residents.

17:02.080 --> 17:04.320
Expand lockdown area to 100 meters.

17:04.321 --> 17:05.287
Yes, sir.

17:09.240 --> 17:10.002
Everyone, please stand back a bit.

17:10.002 --> 17:11.650
Don't obstruct police from working.

17:12.520 --> 17:14.170
Officer Cheung, your tools.

17:14.240 --> 17:15.127
Thank you.

17:15.760 --> 17:16.439
Officer Cheung.

17:16.440 --> 17:17.406
Will you put on the EOD suit?

17:17.407 --> 17:19.880
You said it could destroy a tank

17:19.960 --> 17:21.405
so, why bother?

18:03.120 --> 18:05.566
Ben, I will drill the nose fuse now

18:05.840 --> 18:06.568
Roger

19:02.280 --> 19:03.319
Ben

19:03.320 --> 19:05.923
I've injected Type 3
fuse coagulant into it.

19:05.924 --> 19:07.570
The fuse should be stabilized

19:07.920 --> 19:09.445
lam starting to remove the fuse

19:09.800 --> 19:10.722
Roger.

20:06.960 --> 20:09.361
Don't be chicken, it is stable

20:11.320 --> 20:12.651
I'm not going back to HQ.

20:12.652 --> 20:13.839
Tell the boss.

20:13.840 --> 20:16.319
After my vacation, I'll
go see him with my report.

20:16.320 --> 20:16.959
Yes, sir.

20:16.960 --> 20:17.643
Thank you

20:18.080 --> 20:18.922
I must go.

20:19.320 --> 20:20.082
Bye, Officer Cheung.

20:21.320 --> 20:22.526
Bye.

20:24.200 --> 20:26.122
Boys and girls, please behave.

20:26.123 --> 20:27.360
- Come here.
- Miss Li.

20:28.040 --> 20:29.679
Don't play on the road.

20:29.680 --> 20:31.039
It's very dangerous.

20:31.040 --> 20:32.599
Good girl.

20:32.600 --> 20:33.249
Come.

20:33.600 --> 20:35.090
Let me give you a "like".

20:40.120 --> 20:41.042
Thank you.

20:41.280 --> 20:42.850
Daddy.

20:44.400 --> 20:45.199
Bye.

20:45.200 --> 20:46.770
Where we go playing?

20:48.120 --> 20:49.879
Are you a parent?

20:49.880 --> 20:51.245
Hello, Miss Li.

20:51.800 --> 20:53.962
Bye.

20:54.320 --> 20:55.401
Do you come to file a complaint against me?

20:55.402 --> 20:56.367
Miss Li.

20:56.560 --> 20:57.891
Bye.

20:58.200 --> 20:59.645
How come you know I teach here?

20:59.646 --> 21:01.688
I forgot to tell you I'm a cop.

21:04.040 --> 21:04.719
Officer.

21:04.720 --> 21:05.528
Miss.

21:06.200 --> 21:07.770
My name is JS Cheung.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.561
Officer Cheung.

21:11.520 --> 21:13.204
If those parents found out

21:14.040 --> 21:15.962
I got stinking drunk in a bar

21:15.963 --> 21:18.084
and was brought to a police station

21:18.085 --> 21:19.525
I don't know what they'll do

21:19.526 --> 21:21.359
I'm normally not like that.

21:21.360 --> 21:22.563
You don't have to tell me

21:22.564 --> 21:23.846
I really don't mind

21:26.040 --> 21:27.644
I've been separated for six months

21:28.120 --> 21:30.202
and just signed the divorce papers

21:31.920 --> 21:35.239
I went to the bar just to drown my sorrows.

21:35.240 --> 21:36.999
Then I wanted to see

21:37.000 --> 21:40.129
if I still "got it".

21:45.560 --> 21:47.289
You can just let me off up ahead.

21:47.290 --> 21:47.959
It's okay.

21:47.960 --> 21:48.881
Where are you going?

21:48.882 --> 21:50.450
I have time to give you a ride.

21:50.840 --> 21:51.727
No, thanks

21:52.040 --> 21:52.927
I don't want to...

21:53.560 --> 21:54.607
But I do.

21:55.840 --> 21:56.966
<i>No</i>

21:57.160 --> 22:00.004
I don't want to get
involved with a taken man

22:00.005 --> 22:01.206
I'm not.

22:06.360 --> 22:07.691
You don't believe me?

22:41.120 --> 22:42.759
In tonight's mission,

22:42.760 --> 22:45.559
an undercover officer helped us

22:45.560 --> 22:47.688
raid an armed robbery organization.

22:47.689 --> 22:49.648
We arrested two suspects.

22:50.440 --> 22:51.521
We have issued

22:52.240 --> 22:54.239
a bounty of HK$5 million

22:54.240 --> 22:56.561
for the arrest of the other suspects

23:04.360 --> 23:08.251
I will wire $50 million
in to your Cayman account.

23:09.640 --> 23:11.399
After I get the money

23:11.400 --> 23:14.119
in a month's time my team will have

23:14.120 --> 23:15.929
trickled into Hong Kong.

23:19.280 --> 23:22.159
And now, our EOD bomb disposal expert.

23:22.160 --> 23:24.208
Superintendent JS Cheung, please.

23:37.680 --> 23:40.331
Please say a few words, Officer Cheung.

23:47.520 --> 23:49.921
Many people ask why I joined EOD

23:50.760 --> 23:52.728
including my girlfriend

23:52.840 --> 23:54.839
I told her a story.

23:54.840 --> 23:57.844
It's called <Belling the Cat>

23:58.400 --> 24:00.359
Long ago, a group of mice

24:00.360 --> 24:03.405
wanted a way to go out of
their hole to find food

24:03.406 --> 24:05.684
without being eaten by the cat outside.

24:05.685 --> 24:06.727
Finally they had an idea:

24:06.728 --> 24:09.087
Hang a bell on the cat.

24:09.800 --> 24:10.845
Every time they hear the bell

24:10.846 --> 24:12.569
they would stay in the
hole, and all will be well.

24:12.570 --> 24:14.239
But the question was

24:14.240 --> 24:17.679
which mouse should hang the bell?

24:17.680 --> 24:18.966
As they were discussing that,

24:18.967 --> 24:21.645
a little mouse raised his hand

24:22.040 --> 24:23.326
and said, "I'll go".

24:24.200 --> 24:25.839
Everyone was curious:

24:25.840 --> 24:27.205
"Why you?"

24:27.800 --> 24:29.006
The little mouse said

24:29.007 --> 24:30.359
in its heart.

24:30.360 --> 24:32.761
Righteousness takes priority over life.

24:33.280 --> 24:36.090
Therefore I chose to be this mouse.

24:39.000 --> 24:40.604
Bomb disposal is not something

24:40.960 --> 24:42.644
you can just do.

24:43.120 --> 24:44.770
It is divine providence

24:47.800 --> 24:49.450
lam very grateful to God

24:51.240 --> 24:54.722
for letting me make
the right choices in every mission

24:56.040 --> 24:57.929
lam very grateful to God

24:58.960 --> 25:00.642
for allowing me to use my life

25:00.643 --> 25:02.130
to protect others' lives.

25:14.440 --> 25:15.521
Hey, girlfriend.

25:15.720 --> 25:17.927
Do I look good dressing up in uniform?

25:17.928 --> 25:19.126
It's okay.

25:19.200 --> 25:20.804
You still look like a bomb disposal expert.

25:20.805 --> 25:21.687
Officer Cheung.

25:22.680 --> 25:23.601
They don't serve coffee.

25:23.602 --> 25:24.647
Drink this instead.

25:25.280 --> 25:25.929
Thank you.

25:26.200 --> 25:26.883
Thank you.

25:27.520 --> 25:29.085
- Congratulations, Officer Chung.
- JS.

25:29.086 --> 25:29.967
Congratulations.

25:29.968 --> 25:32.399
Today you've finally waited long...

25:32.400 --> 25:33.970
What was that?

25:34.920 --> 25:36.206
I was talking gibberish.

25:36.207 --> 25:37.199
Stop that crap.

25:37.200 --> 25:39.441
Let's drink to a pretty woman first.

25:39.442 --> 25:41.647
Officer Cheung seldom brings girlfriend.

25:41.840 --> 25:42.762
What is your name?

25:42.960 --> 25:43.563
Carmen.

25:44.880 --> 25:45.881
It's Miss Li.

25:46.040 --> 25:47.079
She's a teacher.

25:47.080 --> 25:47.959
A teacher!

25:47.960 --> 25:48.679
Yes.

25:48.680 --> 25:50.011
A match made in heaven.

25:50.012 --> 25:51.161
Of course.

25:51.280 --> 25:53.248
In any case, congratulations.

25:53.320 --> 25:54.160
- Congratulations.
- Cheers.

25:54.161 --> 25:55.366
- Congrats to Officer Cheung.
- Cheers.

25:56.560 --> 25:57.925
How long have you known each other?

25:57.926 --> 25:58.999
About a year.

25:59.000 --> 26:00.044
You've been tight-lipped

26:00.045 --> 26:01.690
I was afraid you'd steal her

26:03.880 --> 26:05.086
I'll drop by in a few days.

26:05.087 --> 26:05.719
Great

26:05.720 --> 26:07.525
I'll cook some special dishes for you.

26:07.526 --> 26:08.169
Bye, Carmen.

26:08.170 --> 26:09.082
Bye-bye.

26:09.960 --> 26:10.847
Let's go.

26:28.640 --> 26:29.562
Oh my God!

26:30.280 --> 26:31.088
It's Officer Chow's car.

26:31.089 --> 26:32.969
Fire!

27:15.960 --> 27:17.086
Here is the report.

27:18.920 --> 27:20.081
It is C-4 explosive.

27:20.082 --> 27:21.286
The initial estimate is that

27:21.440 --> 27:24.919
the bomb was attached by magnet to the car.

27:24.920 --> 27:26.405
But it was not a time bomb

27:26.406 --> 27:28.209
nor triggered by starting the engine

27:28.360 --> 27:31.039
but by short-distance remote control.

27:31.040 --> 27:32.963
The killer was at the site.

27:34.120 --> 27:35.645
At least not far away.

27:36.160 --> 27:39.045
He wanted to watch Officer
Chow's car explode.

27:39.046 --> 27:40.403
We think the motive was revenge.

27:40.404 --> 27:42.289
When I was undercover back then.

27:42.680 --> 27:44.728
Officer Chow was my handler.

27:47.040 --> 27:50.249
At first, he wanted me
for the UC assignment

27:51.400 --> 27:54.119
but Hong was famous for explosives

27:54.120 --> 27:55.999
so he found you in EOD.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.570
Peng Hong.

27:58.080 --> 27:59.286
Well

27:59.720 --> 28:01.039
I'll get him caught.

28:01.040 --> 28:02.724
If it's really Peng Hong.

28:02.800 --> 28:04.525
He'll will come for you anyway.

28:04.526 --> 28:06.329
You took my place back then

28:06.330 --> 28:08.399
I must ensure your safety now

28:08.400 --> 28:10.289
I'll assign 24-hour protection for you

28:11.880 --> 28:13.609
I can take care of myself.

28:16.840 --> 28:17.727
Yes.

28:19.120 --> 28:19.962
All right

28:20.920 --> 28:21.967
I'm on my way.

28:23.120 --> 28:23.882
Hello?

28:25.640 --> 28:29.247
(Beware of Bomb)

28:30.040 --> 28:30.879
lam so sorry...

28:30.880 --> 28:31.767
It's very dangerous here.

28:31.768 --> 28:33.283
Please leave the premises now.

28:33.284 --> 28:35.328
Excuse us, please leave the premises now.

28:35.520 --> 28:38.364
Attention, all units.
Evacuate everyone now...

28:38.560 --> 28:40.449
No one is allowed to enter the blockade.

28:41.040 --> 28:43.008
Attention all units...

28:43.200 --> 28:45.159
Evacuate...

28:45.160 --> 28:46.889
Run! Get out!

28:47.720 --> 28:49.279
Evacuate, go.

28:49.280 --> 28:50.925
Keep moving, everyone leave.

28:50.926 --> 28:52.649
Allow the fire trucks in...

29:25.280 --> 29:27.799
Mercury detonator, how creative.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.086
Use the electronic x-ray machine.

29:29.087 --> 29:30.002
Yes, sir.

29:30.880 --> 29:32.245
This is the primer.

29:34.320 --> 29:37.244
This square should be C-4.

29:37.400 --> 29:38.925
Not suitable for on-site neutralization.

29:38.926 --> 29:41.044
It is a timed Improvised Explosive Device

29:41.045 --> 29:42.201
of very high lethality.

29:43.080 --> 29:44.570
When will it explode?

29:46.320 --> 29:47.839
The timer is blocked

29:47.840 --> 29:48.887
I cannot see it well.

29:49.520 --> 29:50.681
Any plan?

29:52.440 --> 29:54.283
Go closer to get a better look.

30:06.880 --> 30:09.244
Officer Kong, I am now
going to examine the IED

30:09.245 --> 30:11.607
I'm handing on-site command
to Number Two, Ben.

30:18.720 --> 30:19.607
Power on.

30:22.200 --> 30:23.361
Here are the tools.

31:10.960 --> 31:11.879
Gum?

31:11.880 --> 31:13.086
How filthy.

31:19.320 --> 31:21.163
Hurry.

31:21.560 --> 31:23.085
It will blow up soon.

31:46.760 --> 31:48.250
One-thousand-one.

31:48.600 --> 31:50.090
One-thousand-two.

31:50.320 --> 31:51.810
One-thousand-three

31:52.600 --> 31:53.399
Ben,

31:53.400 --> 31:55.926
I estimate the IED will
explode in 10 minutes.

31:56.160 --> 31:57.922
It may be dangerous to move it

31:57.923 --> 31:59.331
I'll take care of it now

32:02.840 --> 32:04.804
I will coagulate the mercury
with low temperature

32:04.805 --> 32:06.039
to stop the explosion.

32:06.040 --> 32:07.644
Prepare the liquid nitrogen.

32:07.760 --> 32:08.439
Yes, sir.

32:08.440 --> 32:09.202
Liquid nitrogen, now.

32:09.203 --> 32:10.042
Now.

32:11.400 --> 32:12.321
Attention all units

32:12.322 --> 32:14.163
100% evacuation is mandatory.

32:19.120 --> 32:20.882
There's someone up there. EOD suspend.

32:20.883 --> 32:22.083
Officer Cheung, suspend action.

32:22.084 --> 32:23.286
Trespassers on site

32:28.160 --> 32:29.161
I'll wait.

32:30.360 --> 32:31.805
Hurry up.

32:32.040 --> 32:33.121
It will blow soon.

32:36.040 --> 32:37.644
We're hereto shoot the bomb.

32:43.280 --> 32:43.962
Out of the way.

32:43.963 --> 32:44.609
Get out of here.

32:44.610 --> 32:45.965
EOD, confirm

32:46.360 --> 32:47.282
evacuation is complete.

32:48.880 --> 32:50.530
Officer Cheung, evacuation complete.

33:24.360 --> 33:25.850
Good job.

33:26.560 --> 33:30.087
But it's not over yet.

33:33.080 --> 33:33.599
Clear

33:33.600 --> 33:34.408
Roger.

33:35.880 --> 33:37.685
Officer Kong, the device has been disarmed.

33:37.686 --> 33:40.283
Do not remove the blockade
until further notice

33:40.284 --> 33:42.408
CSI colleagues, you may
begin to gather evidence.

33:51.640 --> 33:52.721
If you put a time bomb here

33:52.722 --> 33:54.046
what time would you set it at?

33:54.047 --> 33:55.041
Of course at lunchtime.

33:55.042 --> 33:55.879
Why?

33:55.880 --> 33:57.211
There are most people here at lunchtime.

33:57.400 --> 33:58.401
The bastard who put it there

33:58.402 --> 34:00.129
would want to create the most casualty.

34:01.880 --> 34:03.564
But it isn't crowded at the time

34:03.565 --> 34:05.210
the bomb was set.

34:05.640 --> 34:06.562
Thank you.

34:15.920 --> 34:16.964
Who called the police?

34:16.965 --> 34:18.246
A man called the police.

34:18.800 --> 34:19.684
All he said was.

34:19.685 --> 34:21.842
"There's a bomb in the
Gloucester Road Garden."

34:23.400 --> 34:25.208
He may have set the bomb.

34:26.760 --> 34:27.841
Calling Officer Kong.

34:28.400 --> 34:30.289
Hazardous object at the
courthouse front door.

34:33.320 --> 34:34.161
Allow me.

34:39.239 --> 34:41.163
C-4, at least three pounds of it.

34:41.639 --> 34:42.971
The circuitry is very complicated.

34:43.040 --> 34:44.246
If it explodes

34:44.880 --> 34:47.565
all the glass in the nearby
buildings will shatter.

34:48.719 --> 34:49.926
How much longer until it explodes?

34:51.760 --> 34:52.518
Three minutes.

34:52.520 --> 34:53.203
There's still time.

34:53.560 --> 34:54.607
- Let's go.
- Officer Kong.

34:54.608 --> 34:57.199
Bomb, make way.

34:57.200 --> 34:59.039
Make way, now!

34:59.040 --> 35:00.405
Give it to me.

35:01.160 --> 35:02.286
Let's go.

35:21.680 --> 35:24.126
It's my first time drifting
with a bomb in my arms.

35:27.600 --> 35:29.011
Will it blow when it's shaken hard?

35:29.012 --> 35:29.799
<i>No.</i>

35:29.800 --> 35:30.599
C-4 is very stable.

35:30.600 --> 35:31.806
It won't blow even when shot at

35:32.600 --> 35:33.726
I've drive faster, then.

35:33.727 --> 35:34.642
Sit tight.

35:44.920 --> 35:45.603
Go!

35:47.000 --> 35:48.331
Make way.

35:48.600 --> 35:49.647
Get out of the way.

35:50.800 --> 35:51.767
Wait.

35:51.960 --> 35:53.121
- Wait.
- What's up?

35:53.122 --> 35:54.406
- Wait.
- There's no time.

35:54.407 --> 35:55.970
- Wait...
- Let's go.

35:57.840 --> 35:58.639
Wait.

35:58.640 --> 35:59.721
Wait a moment.

36:00.560 --> 36:01.368
Ready?

36:01.440 --> 36:02.601
Hurry!

36:02.800 --> 36:03.562
Okay?

36:04.280 --> 36:04.963
Yes.

36:08.600 --> 36:09.283
Run!

36:23.440 --> 36:25.204
You wanted a picture to post on Facebook?

36:27.560 --> 36:28.879
As a souvenir.

36:28.880 --> 36:30.166
Are you nuts?

36:32.240 --> 36:34.679
Two bomb threats in a row.

36:34.680 --> 36:36.006
He is provoking the Police.

36:36.007 --> 36:37.725
We've found out the call to the police

36:37.726 --> 36:40.041
was made from a phone booth at the Garden.

36:40.042 --> 36:41.845
Both bombs and the murder of Officer Chow

36:41.846 --> 36:43.246
look to be the work of one person

36:43.247 --> 36:45.524
I suspect it is the fugitive Peng Hong

36:45.525 --> 36:46.803
I worked with him for two years.

36:46.804 --> 36:47.961
Knowing his personality.

36:47.962 --> 36:50.361
For sure, there should be more to come.

36:50.362 --> 36:52.886
About the bomb discovery case yesterday

36:53.320 --> 36:55.163
I have made it first priority for my men

36:55.280 --> 36:56.805
to crack the case as soon as possible.

36:57.880 --> 37:00.039
The Police never allow anyone

37:00.040 --> 37:01.804
to undermine the security of Hong Kong.

37:27.640 --> 37:28.721
You didn't sleep?

37:31.320 --> 37:32.810
I dozed off for a while.

37:38.000 --> 37:39.206
Sleep some more

37:39.920 --> 37:41.410
I go make you breakfast

37:41.411 --> 37:43.368
wake you up when it's ready.

38:14.880 --> 38:16.086
You're up?

38:18.800 --> 38:21.929
I am making you breakfast in bed.

38:24.400 --> 38:25.401
Let me help.

38:42.680 --> 38:43.602
You'll cook??

38:46.280 --> 38:47.725
Egg (bomb) disposal expert

38:55.600 --> 38:58.046
I've watched a lot of superhero movies.

38:58.400 --> 38:59.925
Girlfriends of superheroes

38:59.926 --> 39:01.888
never end up well.

39:01.960 --> 39:03.166
That's right.

39:03.360 --> 39:04.646
It's a hard life.

39:05.760 --> 39:06.921
Sorry.

39:07.800 --> 39:09.529
You know I've just divorced

39:10.120 --> 39:11.281
I don't want to walk out from one nightmare

39:11.282 --> 39:13.044
into another one

39:19.120 --> 39:20.884
I've thought about that for you.

39:20.885 --> 39:22.006
Why don't we...

39:23.240 --> 39:24.605
just let it go?

39:25.840 --> 39:26.762
Great.

39:27.320 --> 39:29.721
We can still be friends.

39:32.080 --> 39:34.560
Like this? Or ordinary friends?

39:35.720 --> 39:36.960
Ordinary friends.

39:39.240 --> 39:41.288
Okay, I'll leave after breakfast.

39:45.120 --> 39:47.043
Do you still want breakfast in bed?

40:09.040 --> 40:10.007
Come...

40:10.280 --> 40:11.441
Don't miss the laser beams.

40:11.442 --> 40:13.359
Ready 1, 2, 3.

40:13.360 --> 40:15.169
Lily, are you having a good time?

40:15.170 --> 40:16.519
Very much so.

40:16.520 --> 40:17.719
Told you.

40:17.720 --> 40:18.846
We're not those shopping tours, and

40:18.847 --> 40:20.330
have lots of time for taking photos.

40:20.331 --> 40:21.321
Thank you.

40:21.440 --> 40:22.566
That's my job to make you happy.

40:23.200 --> 40:24.281
Mr. Chan, did you take your medicine?

40:24.800 --> 40:25.720
I was having such a good time

40:25.721 --> 40:26.685
I forgot to take my medicine.

40:26.686 --> 40:28.125
Get in the bus. I'll get you some water.

40:28.440 --> 40:29.439
You're so nice.

40:29.440 --> 40:30.009
You're most welcome.

40:30.010 --> 40:32.446
We'll cross the harbor
and go back to the hotel now.

40:32.447 --> 40:33.079
Okay...

40:33.080 --> 40:34.445
Let's go, Chuen.

40:35.280 --> 40:36.441
Sit tight...

40:48.000 --> 40:48.799
Mr. Chiu.

40:48.800 --> 40:49.528
Yes.

40:49.640 --> 40:51.210
Let's go to my friend's
bar on Hong Kong side

40:51.280 --> 40:53.399
and watch the game there.

40:53.400 --> 40:55.050
My son will treat this evening.

40:55.120 --> 40:56.559
Great.

40:56.560 --> 40:58.439
We're all retirees.

40:58.440 --> 41:00.839
You have a job, so you pay.

41:00.840 --> 41:01.639
Thank you.

41:01.640 --> 41:02.641
You're welcome

41:05.120 --> 41:05.882
Uncle Chiu.

41:09.400 --> 41:10.242
What do you think?

41:10.760 --> 41:12.364
I wish I had a son like you.

41:12.365 --> 41:13.282
Let me see.

41:13.840 --> 41:15.365
You heard that?

41:16.040 --> 41:16.689
What are you doing?

41:16.690 --> 41:17.559
No need to ask.

41:17.560 --> 41:18.891
It must be my birthday gift, right?

41:18.892 --> 41:19.639
<i>No.</i>

41:19.640 --> 41:20.801
- Thank you, son.
- It's not.

41:42.600 --> 41:43.522
Mr. Au.

41:43.880 --> 41:45.166
An accident just happened
inside the Tunnel.

41:48.080 --> 41:50.651
We will now close the Kowloon-bound tube.

42:04.200 --> 42:06.199
My boss just told me.

42:06.200 --> 42:08.009
There's been a problem inside this Tunnel.

42:08.010 --> 42:11.839
So they will use the
one-tube-two-way operation.

42:11.840 --> 42:12.919
You can imagine.

42:12.920 --> 42:14.719
You have two nostrils, one is stuffed up.

42:14.720 --> 42:16.210
Of course it won't go as freely as usual.

42:16.211 --> 42:18.282
Sorry that we have to spend some time here.

42:20.920 --> 42:22.206
Traffic jam again?

42:22.720 --> 42:25.246
It's early, we have plenty of time.

42:26.360 --> 42:29.565
There are three cross-harbor
tunnels in Hong Kong.

42:29.566 --> 42:31.399
This Cross-Harbour Tunnel, the Eastern

42:31.400 --> 42:32.606
and the Western Harbour Crossings.

42:32.607 --> 42:34.439
It's cheapest to take Cross-Harbour Tunnel.

42:34.440 --> 42:35.771
The Eastern Harbour
Crossing is more expensive.

42:35.772 --> 42:38.001
But the most expensive is
the Western Harbour Crossing.

42:38.002 --> 42:38.967
It is so expensive

42:38.968 --> 42:41.167
we call it the Tycoons' Tunnel.

42:43.440 --> 42:45.085
Finally we're inside the Tunnel.

42:45.086 --> 42:45.921
We'll be there soon.

42:45.922 --> 42:47.251
Everybody enjoys the trip

42:59.800 --> 43:01.006
I'm in place.

43:01.080 --> 43:01.922
COPY

43:04.920 --> 43:05.807
Block the Tunnel.

43:05.808 --> 43:06.642
COPY

43:24.120 --> 43:25.406
Who taught you how to drive?

43:25.680 --> 43:26.519
Sit still.

43:26.520 --> 43:27.931
Get back in your car.

43:33.640 --> 43:34.641
Nothing serious.

43:38.000 --> 43:38.762
Go.

43:39.600 --> 43:40.328
Go.

43:40.440 --> 43:41.407
Get out of the car.

43:41.600 --> 43:42.328
Go.

43:46.520 --> 43:47.806
- What's going on?
- Let's go.

43:50.120 --> 43:52.043
Stay in your car.

43:53.440 --> 43:54.919
Back in your car, now.

43:54.920 --> 43:56.046
Don't move.

43:58.560 --> 43:59.641
The Tunnel has been blocked.

43:59.642 --> 44:00.926
They all have guns.

44:05.880 --> 44:06.688
Hey.

44:06.920 --> 44:07.762
What are you doing?

44:08.600 --> 44:09.681
I said, get back in the bus!

44:09.682 --> 44:11.045
- Where are you going?
- Sorry...

44:12.920 --> 44:13.719
Sorry.

44:13.720 --> 44:14.685
He don't (doesn't) speak English.

44:14.686 --> 44:15.522
He don't talk (doesn't speak) English.

44:15.523 --> 44:16.885
Get him back in the bus now.

44:16.886 --> 44:18.159
Okay...

44:18.160 --> 44:19.199
Back to the bus.

44:19.200 --> 44:20.281
What's going on?

44:20.282 --> 44:21.327
Get in the bus.

44:23.440 --> 44:24.441
Get in the bus.

44:24.600 --> 44:26.204
Get back in the car.

44:28.760 --> 44:29.727
What's going on?

44:30.360 --> 44:31.239
What's up?

44:31.240 --> 44:32.571
Don't you move.

44:32.960 --> 44:34.199
Don't think about it.

44:34.200 --> 44:35.565
Get back in your cars.

44:35.566 --> 44:37.642
Be quiet...

44:46.880 --> 44:48.166
I said, get back in the car.

44:48.167 --> 44:49.605
Stay in that car.

44:51.000 --> 44:52.650
Put your hands on the wheel.

45:04.880 --> 45:06.839
This is retired police officer 58698

45:06.840 --> 45:08.126
lam trapped in the Cross-Harbour Tunnel.

45:08.127 --> 45:10.159
There are dozens of armed men.

45:10.160 --> 45:11.844
- Their motive is still unclear.
- They're coming.

45:14.720 --> 45:15.607
Phone.

45:19.360 --> 45:20.361
And yours?

45:21.120 --> 45:21.848
Phone.

45:22.840 --> 45:23.682
Hurry.

45:24.360 --> 45:25.646
Come on... Mobile.

45:26.880 --> 45:28.041
Listen carefully.

45:28.520 --> 45:29.806
My name is Blast

45:30.200 --> 45:32.771
I have hundreds of hostages here

45:34.200 --> 45:35.725
and lots of explosives.

45:36.000 --> 45:37.684
Look at me...

45:38.080 --> 45:38.919
Look here.

45:38.920 --> 45:39.921
Your turn, look at me.

45:40.800 --> 45:41.528
How are you?

45:43.000 --> 45:43.921
Come on, say "Cheese".

45:43.922 --> 45:45.922
Look at the camera, look at me.

45:57.960 --> 46:00.008
They are putting something
on the emergency doors.

46:11.360 --> 46:13.799
Emergency call service
has received dozens of calls.

46:13.800 --> 46:15.190
The telecommunications company has verified

46:15.280 --> 46:16.819
that all are come from
the Cross-Harbour Tunnel.

46:16.820 --> 46:17.851
A retired police officer

46:17.852 --> 46:18.919
also called

46:18.920 --> 46:20.445
we believe that he has become a hostage.

46:20.680 --> 46:22.804
The man in charge called himself "Blast".

46:22.805 --> 46:25.403
We are not sure yet
if he is the suspect of Officer Chow case

46:25.404 --> 46:27.205
or the Wanchai explosion case

46:27.206 --> 46:29.806
I suspect the container truck accident in

46:30.280 --> 46:31.519
another side of the
Tunnel is part of the pot.

46:31.520 --> 46:32.851
The driver is Au Kam Keung.

46:32.960 --> 46:34.359
His record is clean.

46:34.360 --> 46:35.599
He is a delivery guy.

46:35.600 --> 46:37.921
But the order was made under a false name.

46:45.280 --> 46:45.919
Sir.

46:45.920 --> 46:46.967
Sir, this way please

46:47.800 --> 46:49.801
I am CIP Regional Crime Unit YW Kong.

46:49.802 --> 46:51.722
This is Senior Assistant
Chief of Police HF Wan.

46:51.723 --> 46:53.519
We request this office
as our Command Center

46:53.520 --> 46:54.851
and want to meet with your engineers.

47:05.560 --> 47:06.800
Wait here for my command.

47:07.840 --> 47:08.682
Yes, Officer Cheung.

47:28.320 --> 47:29.651
Nothing much is happening for now.

47:29.652 --> 47:30.919
- Lam.
- Yes

47:30.920 --> 47:32.649
send the draft to the papers, be quick.

47:33.520 --> 47:36.086
We have some terrifying and terrible news.

47:36.087 --> 47:38.241
There has been reported
terrorists attack here

47:38.242 --> 47:39.969
behind me in the Kowloon Tunnel...

47:44.320 --> 47:45.401
Sorry, sir.

47:46.160 --> 47:47.359
Camera Two.

47:47.360 --> 47:48.691
Zoom in for a closer look.

47:55.920 --> 47:57.809
That's him, Peng Hong.

48:05.440 --> 48:06.965
That could be plastic explosives.

48:07.560 --> 48:08.966
He's showing it to us on purpose

48:08.967 --> 48:11.004
before he destroyed the
surveillance cameras.

48:11.005 --> 48:12.326
The Cross-Harbour Tunnel

48:12.327 --> 48:14.368
was built using the caisson method

48:14.369 --> 48:17.919
and made up of 15 double-tube segments.

48:17.920 --> 48:19.959
Its total length is 1.86km.

48:19.960 --> 48:21.959
Between the two vehicle tubes

48:21.960 --> 48:24.599
is an engineering tube for maintenance.

48:24.600 --> 48:27.203
Along the Tunnel there
are 15 emergency doors

48:27.204 --> 48:29.122
that connect the two vehicle tubes

48:29.123 --> 48:30.929
ls there a drainage system or

48:31.160 --> 48:32.571
air vent that we can use for an attack?

48:32.720 --> 48:34.529
There are hundreds of hostages inside.

48:34.530 --> 48:35.679
Their safety

48:35.680 --> 48:36.886
is our first priority.

48:38.000 --> 48:38.599
Officer Kong

48:38.600 --> 48:40.125
someone just ran out from
the tube on the right.

48:43.000 --> 48:44.079
Who are they?

48:44.080 --> 48:45.283
Our colleagues in Maintenance.

48:45.284 --> 48:47.328
They must have been hiding
in the engineering tube.

49:05.080 --> 49:07.321
Go... Let's go...

49:08.080 --> 49:09.319
Move out! Let's go!

49:09.320 --> 49:11.399
Get back in the car...

49:11.400 --> 49:12.242
Watch out.

49:17.280 --> 49:18.361
Go...

49:18.560 --> 49:19.721
Clear out.

49:39.880 --> 49:41.450
All units, cover Officer Kong.

50:16.360 --> 50:17.646
Officer Kong, get in the car.

50:22.920 --> 50:24.046
Drive, hurry.

50:32.080 --> 50:33.650
Hold fire, back off.

50:40.280 --> 50:42.123
This is Police Commander HF Wan

50:42.440 --> 50:43.930
I want to talk to Blast

50:43.931 --> 50:45.559
I am Blast.

50:45.560 --> 50:46.846
We need to talk.

50:48.080 --> 50:50.241
You're in no position to negotiate with me

50:50.242 --> 50:52.004
I have hundreds of hostages here.

50:52.120 --> 50:53.201
What do you want'?

50:53.202 --> 50:55.646
You have a bomb disposal expert, right?

50:55.647 --> 50:58.439
His badge number is 63489

50:58.440 --> 51:00.010
I will only talk to him.

51:01.080 --> 51:03.199
About 15 minutes ago

51:03.200 --> 51:04.999
at the Cross-Harbour Tunnel toll plaza

51:05.000 --> 51:06.161
there was an intense gunfight and

51:06.162 --> 51:08.603
an explosion suspected to
be caused by terrorists.

51:08.604 --> 51:10.728
As of now, we don't have
any figure on casualties

51:10.840 --> 51:13.446
but I just saw several bloodied policemen.

51:14.600 --> 51:16.759
(Be careful)

51:16.760 --> 51:19.411
Police do not deny
it may be the work of terrorists.

51:20.400 --> 51:22.084
We don't know exactly
what they are aiming for.

51:22.200 --> 51:25.170
There are numerous armed
policemen ready for combat.

51:36.600 --> 51:39.331
(I believe you can)

52:17.320 --> 52:18.731
Don't move.

52:38.760 --> 52:39.841
All these years

